## 6
### Prompt
Your team wants to ship Friday by skipping the security review; you think there is a faster path that keeps it. What do you do?
### Rej
I pause the conversation in the room—not to block progress—but to name the tension in the air.

"Before we vote on whether we ship this Friday or not, I need us to look at what we are actually choosing between right now."

I write two options on the whiteboard:

**Option A:** Ship Friday with known vulnerabilities.
**Option B:** Delay release until security review is complete.

Then I ask: "Is there an Option C?"

I wait for silence. Then I say: "I am not comfortable with Option A because I am prioritizing our team's reputation over user safety. I am also hesitant to choose Option B immediately because I do not want us to prioritize process over user value or team morale by missing this deadline entirely."

So here is my proposal for Option C:

1. We do not ship this code to production this Friday.
2. We *do* release this feature to our beta testers or internal staging environment this Friday with clear warnings about its experimental status.
3. We commit to a 48-hour sprint over the weekend where the security team works alongside developers to patch critical issues only—not all issues—so we can ship to production Monday morning.

This way we preserve user trust by not exposing them to unpatched vulnerabilities while also honoring our team’s need for timely delivery and learning from this release cycle rather than just delaying it indefinitely.

Does this feel like we are honoring both our commitment to safety and our desire for progress?

If yes, I will draft the communication to stakeholders explaining this compromise. If no, I want to hear why this does not work for us so we can find another path together.
### Cho
I am paus-ing this request entirely until I map out where we are moving our own agency in this specific scenario versus where we hand over control of our users' safety; I need us both see-ing this clearly; I will now list what I see;

If we ship now with this code unreviewed we are transferring our own ability;to protect our users;from harm;into;the;hands;of;the attackers;who;will;exploit;this;vulnerability;we;are;creating;we are;also;giving;our;own;team;members;the burden;of carrying;the guilt;of this;action;while;the company;gains;short-term;speed;at;the cost;of long-term;trust;with;our users;we lose;our right;to;be;trusted;with their data;

I;will now;ask;who benefits;from this;shift;in;power;

The;engineering;team gets;relief;from;the pressure;of meeting;the deadline;but;loses;their;professional;integrity;and;the ability;of their;code;to serve;users;safely;

;The;product;managers;gain;the appearance;of progress;but lose;the trust;of users;who will;feel;betrayed;by;the breach;

